<p>
    Two facts are load-bearing for the forks: the regression happened <em>on enforced routes</em> during the
    riskiest edit class (a conversion), and the warn-only violations were first <em>seen</em> by this prep&rsquo;s
    measurement run &mdash; advisory output is ignored in practice, exactly the failure mode the baseline
    literature warns about.
</p>

<h2>Prior art</h2>
<we-data-table>
<table class="data-table">
    <thead>
        <tr><th>Pattern</th><th>Incumbents</th><th>Strength</th><th>Documented weakness</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Per-route warn&#8594;enforce ratchet</strong> (ours today)</td>
            <td>pa11y-ci <code>threshold</code>/<code>--level</code>; Lighthouse CI assertion budgets</td>
            <td>Deterministic, reviewable route-granular set; never blocks a surface that hasn&rsquo;t earned it</td>
            <td>Fail-open for unpromoted/new routes; advisory output goes unread (measured here)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Violation-level baseline snapshot</strong></td>
            <td>trivago&rsquo;s baseline-driven axe reporting; microsoft/accessibility-insights-action baselining;
                cfn-lint baseline feature request</td>
            <td>Immediate fail-on-<em>new</em> everywhere, day one, without draining historical debt first</td>
            <td>Churn-sensitive (accessibility-insights-action issue 949 &mdash; node fingerprints break on
                unrelated DOM changes); snapshotted debt rots with no drain forcing-function</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Invert at the drained milestone</strong></td>
            <td>TypeScript strict-flag migrations; ESLint suppression burn-downs (fail-closed default + explicit
                exception list once clean)</td>
            <td>Fail-closed for everything new; the exception list is explicit, visible, and temporary</td>
            <td>Needs a concrete drain trigger, else it&rsquo;s a perpetual &ldquo;someday&rdquo;</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
</we-data-table>

<h2>Recommendation (folded into #867&rsquo;s forks)</h2>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Fork 1 &mdash; decoupled promotion.</strong> Any measured-green scope-C route enters
        <code>ENFORCED_ROUTES</code> immediately, regardless of whether its FUI conversion has landed. The gate
        asserts WCAG on the rendered DOM whatever renders it; promoting early means each later conversion lands
        <em>under enforcement</em> &mdash; the dogfood proof made structural. Holding promotion until conversion
        leaves the riskiest edit unguarded; the measured 5-route regression is the smoking gun, and the
        hold-branch&rsquo;s remaining defense (&ldquo;don&rsquo;t enforce markup about to be rewritten&rdquo;) is
        churn/cost, not merit.</li>
    <li><strong>Fork 2 &mdash; drain, then invert.</strong> Keep #774&rsquo;s warn-only entry while the current
        set drains; once <code>ENFORCED_ROUTES</code> equals the derived set and the lane is green, flip to
        enforce-by-default with an explicit <code>WARN_ROUTES</code> exception set (new/experimental surfaces opt
        <em>out</em>, visibly and temporarily). This supersedes #774&rsquo;s warn-only-entry rider from that
        milestone while preserving its real invariant (never silently un-earn enforcement; the set stays explicit
        and reviewable &mdash; now as exceptions). The violation-baseline alternative is rejected on merit (churn
        sensitivity + debt-rot + #774&rsquo;s route-granular explicit-set precedent).</li>
    <li><strong>Not decisions:</strong> promotion mechanism (manual set edit vs a helper
        <code>--list-promotable</code> report &mdash; coexist; optional tooling), remediation order (pure
        prioritization), and FUI-drain slicing. The ruled policy applies per-repo, mirrored not shared
        (#774/#849 precedent).</li>
</ol>

<h2>Classification &amp; boundary note</h2>
<p>
    Everything here concerns the WE <strong>website app</strong> (the 11ty docs site and its Playwright gate,
    <code>we:tests/a11y/*</code>) and the FUI website&rsquo;s mirror gate &mdash; repo CI/devtools policy, kin to
    <code>check:standards</code>. Nothing rules on the zero-impl WE standard layer; no protocol is minted (axe is
    the WCAG engine, the sitemap is the sitemaps.org artifact &mdash; both consumed, not re-specified); no
    vocab&#8594;component mapping is created (the conversions were ruled in #865/#866/#2018&ndash;#2021).
</p>

